 Mojafela Dlamini (24), Nkosingiphile Khoza (24), Bhekinkosi Simeon Thabethe (34), and Sbusiso Thabethe (38) are facing charges of murder. It is alleged the men stabbed the deceased with a knife at the Iraq Taxi Rank. A photo of Bhekinkosi Simeon Thabethe, one of the accused. According to the police report, the deceased was transported to the Middelburg Provincial Hospital by his friend but died on arrival. He had two stab wounds. It is not clear what led to the incident. The accused remain in police custody. A photo of Mojafela Dlamini, one of the accused. Also read: Wet Sangoma drying in cell • One of the accused, Sibusiso Thabethe, a self-proclaimed sangoma, fooled police in 2014 into believing he drowned. Police launched a massive search and rescue operation. He was arrested for attempted murder, kidnapping and possession of an unlicensed firearm and ammunition, but was only charged for having an unlicensed firearm. A photo of Nkosingiphile Khoza, one of the accused. Major General among N4 road casualties Duur petrol nou gesog vir diewe Man hijacked on N4 VIDEO: Video wys Vivian was onskuldig  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za Click here to subscribe to a bi-weekly newsletter of local, national and international news